The 34th century BC was a century which lasted from the year 3400 BC to 3301 BC.

Cultures[edit]

  • Stage IIIa2 of the Naqada culture in Egypt (dated in 1998).
  • Archaic forms of the cuneiform script emerge in the late Uruk period in Mesopotamia.

Religion[edit]

  • Enoch (c. 3382 BC – disappeared 3017 BC), according to the Hebrew Bible
  • Methuselah (c. 3317 – 2348 BC), according to the Hebrew Bible
